at the low energy, parallel spin\nstripe fluctuations for optimally doped x = 0.19 display dynamic spectral\nweight which grows with decreasing temperature and saturates below its\nsuperconducting T$_c$. The elastic order parameter for x = 0.19 also shows\nplateau behavior coincident with the onset of superconductivity. This set of\nobservations assert the foundational role played by two dimensional parallel\nspin stripe order and fluctuations in High T$_c$ cuprate superconductivity.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 10 Sep 2020 01:41:28 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-06-02"}
