 exceptionally low noise levels for beta Cas. The star is also one\nof very few delta Scuti pulsators known to date to show a measurable magnetic\nfield, and the first delta Scuti star with a dynamo magnetic field. These\ncharacteristics make beta Cas an interesting target for future studies of\ndynamo processes in the thin convective envelopes of F-type stars, of the\ntransition region between fossil and dynamo fields, and the interaction between\npulsations and magnetic field.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 10 Sep 2020 11:36:32 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-11-11"}
